function GetGreatVersesData(){return GreatVerses.data}var GreatVerses={data:[{scriptures:"Ephesians\\4:26-27",id:"1",title:"Anger",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:26-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  Be angry, and don't sin. Don't let the sun go down on your wrath,\r {BR}27  neither give place to the devil.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Ephesians\\4:29-29",id:"2",title:"Bad Language",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:29-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  Let no corrupt speech proceed out of your mouth, but such as is good for building up as the need may be, that it may give grace to those who hear.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Matthew\\5:3-11",id:"3",title:"Blessings in Christ",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\5:3-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  {I}{B}Blessed are the poor in spirit, for theirs is the Kingdom of Heaven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}4  {I}{B}Blessed are those who mourn, for they shall be comforted.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}5  {I}{B}Blessed are the gentle, for they shall inherit the earth.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}6  {I}{B}Blessed are those who hunger and thirst after righteousness, for they shall be filled.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}7  {I}{B}Blessed are the merciful, for they shall obtain mercy.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}8  {I}{B}Blessed are the pure in heart, for they shall see God.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}9  {I}{B}Blessed are the peacemakers, for they shall be called children of God.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}10  {I}{B}Blessed are those who have been persecuted for righteousness' sake, for theirs is the Kingdom of Heaven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}11  {I}{B}Blessed are you when people reproach you, persecute you, and say all kinds of evil against you falsely, for my sake.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"John\\14:6-6",id:"4",title:"Christ Alone",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Jesus said to him, {I}{B}I am the way, the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father, except through me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Isaiah\\53:6-6",id:"5",title:"Christ Our Substitute",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\53:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  All we like sheep have gone astray. Everyone has turned to his own way; and Yahweh has laid on him the iniquity of us all.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Colossians\\1:15-17",id:"6",title:"Christ the Creator",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\1:15-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  who is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn of all creation.\r {BR}16  For by him all things were created, in the heavens and on the earth, things visible and things invisible, whether thrones or dominions or principalities or powers; all things have been created through him, and for him.\r {BR}17  He is before all things, and in him all things are held together.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"2 Corinthians\\1:3-4",id:"7",title:"Comfort",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\1:3-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of mercies and God of all comfort;\r {BR}4  who comforts us in all our affliction, that we may be able to comfort those who are in any affliction, through the comfort with which we ourselves are comforted by God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Exodus\\20:12-17",id:"8",title:"Commandments",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\20:12-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Honor your father and your mother, that your days may be long in the land which Yahweh your God gives you.\r {BR}13  You shall not murder.\r {BR}14  You shall not commit adultery.\r {BR}15  You shall not steal.\r {BR}16  You shall not give false testimony against your neighbor.\r {BR}17  You shall not covet your neighbor's house. You shall not covet your neighbor's wife, nor his male servant, nor his female servant, nor his ox, nor his donkey, nor anything that is your neighbor's.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"2 Chronicles\\16:9-9",id:"9",title:"Commitment",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Chronicles\\16:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  For the eyes of Yahweh run back and forth throughout the whole earth, to show himself strong in the behalf of them whose heart is perfect toward him. Herein you have done foolishly; for from henceforth you shall have wars.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Romans\\12:1-2",id:"10",title:"Commitment to God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\12:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Therefore I urge you, brothers, by the mercies of God, to present your bodies a living sacrifice, holy, acceptable to God, which is your spiritual service.\r {BR}2  Don't be conformed to this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your mind, so that you may prove what is the good, well-pleasing, and perfect will of God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"1 John\\1:9-9",id:"11",title:"Confession/Forgiveness",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\1:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  If we confess our sins, he is faithful and righteous to forgive us the sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Habakkuk\\3:19-19",id:"12",title:"Confidence in God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Habakkuk\\3:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Yahweh, the Lord, is my strength. He makes my feet like deer's feet, and enables me to go in high places. For the music director, on my stringed instruments.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Joshua\\1:9-9",id:"13",title:"Courage",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Joshua\\1:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Haven't I commanded you? Be strong and of good courage. Don't be afraid, neither be dismayed: for Yahweh your God is with you wherever you go.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\19:1-1",id:"14",title:"Creation",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\19:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  The heavens declare the glory of God. The expanse shows his handiwork.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Galatians\\6:9-9",id:"15",title:"Discouragement",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\6:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Let us not be weary in doing good, for we will reap in due season, if we don't give up.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Ecclesiastes\\12:13-14",id:"16",title:"Duty/Fear of God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ecclesiastes\\12:13-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  This is the end of the matter. All has been heard. Fear God, and keep his commandments; for this is the whole duty of man.\r {BR}14  For God will bring every work into judgment, with every hidden thing, whether it is good, or whether it is evil.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Micah\\6:8-8",id:"17",title:"Duty/Righteousness",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Micah\\6:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  He has shown you, O man, what is good. What does Yahweh require of you, but to act justly, to love mercy, and to walk humbly with your God?\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Proverbs\\1:8-8",id:"18",title:"Education/Obeying Parents",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\1:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  My son, listen to your father's instruction, and don't forsake your mother's teaching:\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Hebrews\\10:24-25",id:"19",title:"Encouragement",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\10:24-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  Let us consider how to provoke one another to love and good works,\r {BR}25  not forsaking our own assembling together, as the custom of some is, but exhorting one another; and so much the more, as you see the Day approaching.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Acts\\16:31-31;Hebrews\\11:1-1",id:"20",title:"Faith",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\16:31-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  They said, Believe in the Lord Jesus Christ, and you will be saved, you and your household.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\11:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Now faith is assurance of things hoped for, proof of things not seen.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Romans\\5:1-2",id:"21",title:"Faith/Peace with God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\5:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Being therefore justified by faith, we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ;\r {BR}2  through whom we also have our access by faith into this grace in which we stand. We rejoice in hope of the glory of God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Ephesians\\6:1-1",id:"22",title:"Family Relationships",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\6:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Children, obey your parents in the Lord, for this is right.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Proverbs\\1:7-7",id:"23",title:"Fear of God/Wisdom",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\1:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  The fear of Yahweh is the beginning of knowledge; but the foolish despise wisdom and instruction.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Isaiah\\41:10-10",id:"24",title:"Fear/Strength",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\41:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Don't you be afraid, for I am with you. Don't be dismayed, for I am your God. I will strengthen you. Yes, I will help you. Yes, I will uphold you with the right hand of my righteousness.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\56:3-4",id:"25",title:"Fear/Trust",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\56:3-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  When I am afraid, I will put my trust in you.\r {BR}4  In God, I praise his word. In God, I put my trust. I will not be afraid. What can flesh do to me?\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Luke\\14:26-27",id:"26",title:"Following Christ",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\14:26-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  {I}{B}If anyone comes to me, and doesn't hate his own father, mother, wife, children, brothers, and sisters, yes, and his own life also, he can't be my disciple.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}27  {I}{B}Whoever doesn't bear his own cross, and come after me, can't be my disciple.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Mark\\11:25-25;Colossians\\3:13-13",id:"27",title:"Forgiveness",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Mark\\11:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  {I}{B}Whenever you stand praying, forgive, if you have anything against anyone; so that your Father, who is in heaven, may also forgive you your transgressions.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\3:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  bearing with one another, and forgiving each other, if any man has a complaint against any; even as Christ forgave you, so you also do.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Proverbs\\18:24-24",id:"28",title:"Friendship",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\18:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  A man of many companions may be ruined, but there is a friend who sticks closer than a brother.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Galatians\\5:22-23",id:"29",title:"Fruit of the Spirit",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\5:22-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faith,\r {BR}23  gentleness, and self-control. Against such things there is no law.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Proverbs\\15:1-1",id:"30",title:"Gentleness/Speech",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\15:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  A gentle answer turns away wrath, but a harsh word stirs up anger.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Deuteronomy\\16:17-17;Malachi\\3:10-10",id:"31",title:"Giving",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\16:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  every man shall give as he is able, according to the blessing of Yahweh your God which he has given you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Malachi\\3:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Bring the whole tithe into the storehouse, that there may be food in my house, and test me now in this, says Yahweh of Armies, if I will not open you the windows of heaven, and pour you out a blessing, that there shall not be room enough for.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"2 Corinthians\\9:7-7",id:"32",title:"Giving Cheerfully",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\9:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Let each man give according as he has determined in his heart; not grudgingly, or under compulsion; for God loves a cheerful giver.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\102:25-27",id:"33",title:"God Is Unchanging",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\102:25-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  Of old, you laid the foundation of the earth. The heavens are the work of your hands.\r {BR}26  They will perish, but you will endure. Yes, all of them will wear out like a garment. You will change them like a cloak, and they will be changed.\r {BR}27  But you are the same. Your years will have no end.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\103:13-13",id:"34",title:"God Our Father",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\103:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Like a father has compassion on his children, so Yahweh has compassion on those who fear him.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\23:1-6",id:"35",title:"God Our Sheperd",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\23:1-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Yahweh is my shepherd: I shall lack nothing.\r {BR}2  He makes me lie down in green pastures. He leads me beside still waters.\r {BR}3  He restores my soul. He guides me in the paths of righteousness for his name's sake.\r {BR}4  Even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil, for you are with me. Your rod and your staff, they comfort me.\r {BR}5  You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies. You anoint my head with oil. My cup runs over.\r {BR}6  Surely goodness and loving kindness shall follow me all the days of my life, and I will dwell in Yahweh's house forever.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Nehemiah\\9:6-6;Psalms\\100:3-3;Psalms\\139:13-16",id:"36",title:"God the Creator",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Nehemiah\\9:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  You are Yahweh, even you alone; you have made heaven, the heaven of heavens, with all their army, the earth and all things that are thereon, the seas and all that is in them, and you preserve them all; and the army of heaven worships you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\100:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Know that Yahweh, he is God. It is he who has made us, and we are his. We are his people, and the sheep of his pasture.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\139:13-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  For you formed my inmost being. You knit me together in my mother's womb.\r {BR}14  I will give thanks to you, for I am fearfully and wonderfully made. Your works are wonderful. My soul knows that very well.\r {BR}15  My frame wasn't hidden from you, when I was made in secret, woven together in the depths of the earth.\r {BR}16  Your eyes saw my body. In your book they were all written, the days that were ordained for me, when as yet there were none of them.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Proverbs\\21:21-21",id:"37",title:"Godliness",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\21:21-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  He who follows after righteousness and kindness finds life, righteousness, and honor.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"1 John\\5:18-18",id:"38",title:"God's Family",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\5:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  We know that whoever is born of God doesn't sin, but he who was born of God keeps himself, and the evil one doesn't touch him.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\30:4-5",id:"39",title:"God's Forgiveness",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\30:4-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Sing praise to Yahweh, you saints of his. Give thanks to his holy name.\r {BR}5  For his anger is but for a moment. His favor is for a lifetime. Weeping may stay for the night, but joy comes in the morning.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"James\\1:17-17",id:"40",title:"God's Goodness",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\James\\1:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights, with whom can be no variation, nor turning shadow.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\19:9-10",id:"41",title:"God's Laws",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\19:9-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  The fear of Yahweh is clean, enduring forever. Yahweh's ordinances are true, and righteous altogether.\r {BR}10  More to be desired are they than gold, yes, than much fine gold; sweeter also than honey and the extract of the honeycomb.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Jeremiah\\31:3-3;Lamentations\\3:22-23;John\\3:16-16",id:"42",title:"God's Love",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\31:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Yahweh appeared of old to me, ({I}{B}saying{/B}{/I}), Yes, I have loved you with an everlasting love: therefore with loving kindness have I drawn you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Lamentations\\3:22-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  ({I}{B}It is of{/B}{/I}) Yahweh's loving kindnesses that we are not consumed, because his compassion doesn't fail.\r {BR}23  They are new every morning; great is your faithfulness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\3:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  {I}{B}For God so loved the world, that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish, but have eternal life.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Jeremiah\\29:11-11;Romans\\8:28-28",id:"43",title:"God's Plan",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\29:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  For I know the thoughts that I think toward you, says Yahweh, thoughts of peace, and not of evil, to give you hope in your latter end.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  We know that all things work together for good for those who love God, to those who are called according to his purpose.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Job\\9:10-10;Isaiah\\55:9-9;2 Corinthians\\4:7-7;Ephesians\\3:20-20",id:"44",title:"God's Power",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\9:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  He does great things past finding out; yes, marvelous things without number.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\55:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  For as the heavens are higher than the earth, so are my ways higher than your ways, and my thoughts than your thoughts.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\4:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  But we have this treasure in clay vessels, that the exceeding greatness of the power may be of God, and not from ourselves.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\3:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  Now to him who is able to do exceedingly abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that works in us,\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\16:8-8",id:"45",title:"God's Presence",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\16:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  I have set Yahweh always before me. Because he is at my right hand, I shall not be moved.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Exodus\\14:14-14;Deuteronomy\\33:27-27;2 Samuel\\22:31-31;Psalms\\3:3-3",id:"46",title:"God's Protection",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\14:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Yahweh will fight for you, and you shall be still.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\33:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  The eternal God is ({I}{B}your{/B}{/I}) dwelling place. Underneath are the everlasting arms. He thrust out the enemy from before you, and said, Destroy.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Samuel\\22:31-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  As for God, his way is perfect. The word of Yahweh is tested. He is a shield to all those who take refuge in him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\3:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  But you, Yahweh, are a shield around me, my glory, and the one who lifts up my head.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"1 Chronicles\\29:11-11;Psalms\\24:1-1",id:"47",title:"God's Reign",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Chronicles\\29:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Yours, Yahweh, is the greatness, the power, the glory, the victory, and the majesty: for all that is in the heavens and in the earth is yours. Yours is the kingdom, Yahweh, and you are exalted as head above all.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\24:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  The earth is Yahweh's, with its fullness; the world, and those who dwell therein.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Hebrews\\4:12-12",id:"48",title:"God's Word",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\4:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  For the word of God is living, and active, and sharper than any two-edged sword, and piercing even to the dividing of soul and spirit, of both joints and marrow, and is able to discern the thoughts and intentions of the heart.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\119:105-105",id:"49",title:"God's Word/Guidance",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:105-105{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}105  Your word is a lamp to my feet, and a light for my path.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Jeremiah\\15:16-16",id:"50",title:"God's Words",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\15:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Your words were found, and I ate them; and your words were to me a joy and the rejoicing of my heart: for I am called by your name, Yahweh, God of Armies.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Romans\\1:16-16",id:"51",title:"Good News",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\1:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  For I am not ashamed of the Good News of Christ, for it is the power of God for salvation for everyone who believes; for the Jew first, and also for the Greek.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Hebrews\\4:16-16",id:"52",title:"Grace/Mercy",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\4:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Let us therefore draw near with boldness to the throne of grace, that we may receive mercy, and may find grace for help in time of need.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\116:15-15",id:"53",title:"Grief at Death",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\116:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Precious in the sight of Yahweh is the death of his saints.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\32:8-8",id:"54",title:"Guidance",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\32:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  I will instruct you and teach you in the way which you shall go. I will counsel you with my eye on you.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Isaiah\\58:11-11",id:"55",title:"Guidance/Provision",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\58:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  and Yahweh will guide you continually, and satisfy your soul in dry places, and make strong your bones; and you shall be like a watered garden, and like a spring of water, whose waters don't fail.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Leviticus\\20:7-7",id:"56",title:"Holiness",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Leviticus\\20:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7   'Sanctify yourselves therefore, and be holy; for I am Yahweh your God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Proverbs\\19:1-1",id:"57",title:"Honesty",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\19:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Better is the poor who walks in his integrity than he who is perverse in his lips and is a fool.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Ecclesiastes\\12:1-1",id:"58",title:"Honoring God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ecclesiastes\\12:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Remember also your Creator in the days of your youth, before the evil days come, and the years draw near, when you will say, I have no pleasure in them;\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Isaiah\\40:6-8",id:"59",title:"Humanity/God's Word",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:6-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  The voice of one saying, Cry! One said, What shall I cry? All flesh is like grass, and all its glory is like the flower of the field.\r {BR}7  The grass withers, the flower fades, because Yahweh's breath blows on it. Surely the people are like grass.\r {BR}8  The grass withers, the flower fades; but the word of our God stands forever.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"2 Chronicles\\7:14-14;James\\4:7-10",id:"60",title:"Humility/Repentance",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Chronicles\\7:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  if my people, who are called by my name, shall humble themselves, and pray, and seek my face, and turn from their wicked ways; then will I hear from heaven, and will forgive their sin, and will heal their land.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\4:7-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Be subject therefore to God. But resist the devil, and he will flee from you.\r {BR}8  Draw near to God, and he will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands, you sinners; and purify your hearts, you double-minded.\r {BR}9  Lament, mourn, and weep. Let your laughter be turned to mourning, and your joy to gloom.\r {BR}10  Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and he will exalt you.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Romans\\1:4-4",id:"61",title:"Jesus",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\1:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  who was declared to be the Son of God with power, according to the Spirit of holiness, by the resurrection from the dead, Jesus Christ our Lord,\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\40:8-8",id:"62",title:"Joy",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\40:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  I delight to do your will, my God. Yes, your law is within my heart.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Philippians\\4:6-6",id:"63",title:"Joy and Peace",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  In nothing be anxious, but in everything, by prayer and petition with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Amos\\5:24-24",id:"64",title:"Justice",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Amos\\5:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  But let justice roll on like rivers, and righteousness like a mighty stream.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"James\\1:19-19",id:"65",title:"Listening/Patience",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\James\\1:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  So, then, my beloved brothers, let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, and slow to anger;\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"1 John\\3:18-19",id:"66",title:"Love in Action",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\3:18-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  My little children, let's not love in word only, neither with the tongue only, but in deed and truth.\r {BR}19  And by this we know that we are of the truth, and persuade our hearts before him,\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Matthew\\5:43-45",id:"67",title:"Love of Enemies",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\5:43-45{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}43  {I}{B}You have heard that it was said, 'You shall love your neighbor, and hate your enemy.'{/B}{/I}\r {BR}44  {I}{B}But I tell you, love your enemies, bless those who curse you, do good to those who hate you, and pray for those who mistreat you and persecute you,{/B}{/I}\r {BR}45  {I}{B}that you may be children of your Father who is in heaven. For he makes his sun to rise on the evil and the good, and sends rain on the just and the unjust.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Luke\\6:31-31;1 Thessalonians\\3:12-12",id:"68",title:"Loving Others",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\6:31-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  {I}{B}As you would like people to do to you, do exactly so to them.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\3:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  and the Lord make you to increase and abound in love one toward another, and toward all men, even as we also do toward you,\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Hebrews\\13:5-6",id:"69",title:"Money",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\13:5-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Be free from the love of money, content with such things as you have, for he has said, I will in no way leave you, neither will I in any way forsake you.\r {BR}6  So that with good courage we say, The Lord is my helper. I will not fear. What can man do to me?\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Job\\36:26-26",id:"70",title:"Mystery of God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\36:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  Behold, God is great, and we don't know him. The number of his years is unsearchable.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Philippians\\4:19-19",id:"71",title:"Needs",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  My God will supply every need of yours according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"2 Corinthians\\5:17-17",id:"72",title:"New Persons",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\5:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Therefore if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. The old things have passed away. Behold, all things have become new.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"1 Samuel\\15:22-22",id:"73",title:"Obedience",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Samuel\\15:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  Samuel said, Has Yahweh as great delight in burnt offerings and sacrifices, as in obeying the voice of Yahweh? Behold, to obey is better than sacrifice, and to listen than the fat of rams.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"1 John\\2:3-6",id:"74",title:"Obeying God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\2:3-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  This is how we know that we know him: if we keep his commandments.\r {BR}4  One who says, I know him, and doesn't keep his commandments, is a liar, and the truth isn't in him.\r {BR}5  But whoever keeps his word, God's love has most certainly been perfected in him. This is how we know that we are in him:\r {BR}6  he who says he remains in him ought himself also to walk just like he walked.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Isaiah\\26:3-3;John\\14:27-27",id:"75",title:"Peace",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\26:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  You will keep whoever's mind is steadfast in perfect peace, because he trusts in you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  {I}{B}Peace I leave with you. My peace I give to you; not as the world gives, give I to you. Don't let your heart be troubled, neither let it be fearful.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Colossians\\3:15-15",id:"76",title:"Peace from Christ",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\3:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  And let the peace of God rule in your hearts, to which also you were called in one body; and be thankful.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"John\\15:18-18",id:"77",title:"Persecution",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\John\\15:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  {I}{B}If the world hates you, you know that it has hated me before it hated you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\116:1-1;Isaiah\\65:24-24;Luke\\11:2-4;1 Thessalonians\\5:17-18",id:"78",title:"Prayer",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\116:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  I love Yahweh, because he listens to my voice, and my cries for mercy.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\65:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  It shall happen that, before they call, I will answer; and while they are yet speaking, I will hear.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\11:2-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  He said to them, {I}{B}When you pray, say, 'Our Father in heaven, may your name be kept holy. May your Kingdom come. May your will be done on Earth, as it is in heaven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}3  {I}{B}Give us day by day our daily bread.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}4  {I}{B}Forgive us our sins, for we ourselves also forgive everyone who is indebted to us. Bring us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one.' {/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\5:17-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Pray without ceasing.\r {BR}18  In everything give thanks, for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus toward you.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\55:16-17",id:"79",title:"Prayer/Rescue",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\55:16-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  As for me, I will call on God. Yahweh will save me.\r {BR}17  Evening, morning, and at noon, I will cry out in distress. He will hear my voice.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Proverbs\\11:2-2",id:"80",title:"Pride/Humility",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\11:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  When pride comes, then comes shame, but with humility comes wisdom.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\51:6-7;Psalms\\86:11-11",id:"81",title:"Purity",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\51:6-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Behold, you desire truth in the inward parts. You teach me wisdom in the inmost place.\r {BR}7  Purify me with hyssop, and I will be clean. Wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\86:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Teach me your way, Yahweh. I will walk in your truth. Make my heart undivided to fear your name.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\119:9-9",id:"82",title:"Purity/God's Word",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  How can a young man keep his way pure? By living according to your word.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Isaiah\\40:29-31",id:"83",title:"Renewed Strength",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:29-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  He gives power to the weak. He increases the strength of him who has no might.\r {BR}30  Even the youths faint and get weary, and the young men utterly fall;\r {BR}31  But those who wait for Yahweh will renew their strength. They will mount up with wings like eagles. They will run, and not be weary. They will walk, and not faint.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Galatians\\6:4-4",id:"84",title:"Responsibility",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\6:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  But let each man test his own work, and then he will take pride in himself and not in his neighbor.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\91:1-1",id:"85",title:"Rest in God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\91:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  He who dwells in the secret place of the Most High will rest in the shadow of the Almighty.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\51:8-10",id:"86",title:"Restoration",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\51:8-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Let me hear joy and gladness, That the bones which you have broken may rejoice.\r {BR}9  Hide your face from my sins, and blot out all of my iniquities.\r {BR}10  Create in me a clean heart, O God. Renew a right spirit within me.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"John\\11:25-25",id:"87",title:"Resurrection",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\John\\11:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  Jesus said to her, {I}{B}I am the resurrection and the life. He who believes in me will still live, even if he dies.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Revelation\\3:20",id:"88",title:"Salavation",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Revelation\\3:20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  {I}{B}Behold, I stand at the door and knock. If anyone hears my voice and opens the door, then I will come in to him, and will dine with him, and he with me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"1 Chronicles\\28:9-9;Isaiah\\55:6-6",id:"89",title:"Seeking God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Chronicles\\28:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  You, Solomon my son, know the God of your father, and serve him with a perfect heart and with a willing mind; for Yahweh searches all hearts, and understands all the imaginations of the thoughts: if you seek him, he will be found by you; but if you forsake him, he will cast you off forever.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\55:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Seek Yahweh while he may be found; call you on him while he is near:\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Matthew\\20:26-28",id:"90",title:"Servant Leadership",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\20:26-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  {I}{B}It shall not be so among you, but whoever desires to become great among you shall be your servant.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}27  {I}{B}Whoever desires to be first among you shall be your bondservant,{/B}{/I}\r {BR}28  {I}{B}even as the Son of Man came not to be served, but to serve, and to give his life as a ransom for many.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Joshua\\24:15-15",id:"91",title:"Serving God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Joshua\\24:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  If it seems evil to you to serve Yahweh, choose this day whom you will serve; whether the gods which your fathers served that were beyond the River, or the gods of the Amorites, in whose land you dwell: but as for me and my house, we will serve Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"1 Thessalonians\\4:3-3",id:"92",title:"Sexual Sin",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\4:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  For this is the will of God: your sanctification, that you abstain from sexual immorality,\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\51:4-5",id:"93",title:"Sin",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\51:4-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Against you, and you only, have I sinned, and done that which is evil in your sight; that you may be proved right when you speak, and justified when you judge.\r {BR}5  Behold, I was brought forth in iniquity. In sin my mother conceived me.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Romans\\3:23-23",id:"94",title:"Sin/Salvation",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\3:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  for all have sinned, and fall short of the glory of God;\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Romans\\6:23-23",id:"95",title:"Spirial Death/Eternal Life",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\6:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  For the wages of sin is death, but the free gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Ephesians\\4:28-28",id:"96",title:"Stealing",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  Let him who stole steal no more; but rather let him labor, working with his hands the thing that is good, that he may have something to give to him who has need.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\46:1-1;Philippians\\4:13-13",id:"97",title:"Strength",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\46:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  God is our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  I can do all things through Christ, who strengthens me.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"1 Corinthians\\10:13-13;Hebrews\\2:18-18",id:"98",title:"Temptation",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\10:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  No temptation has taken you except what is common to man. God is faithful, who will not allow you to be tempted above what you are able, but will with the temptation also make the way of escape, that you may be able to endure it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\2:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  For in that he himself has suffered being tempted, he is able to help those who are tempted.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\96:3-3",id:"99",title:"Testimony",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\96:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Declare his glory among the nations, his marvelous works among all the peoples.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\9:1-1;Psalms\\92:1-1",id:"100",title:"Thankfulness",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\9:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  I will give thanks to Yahweh with my whole heart. I will tell of all your marvelous works.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\92:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  It is a good thing to give thanks to Yahweh, to sing praises to your name, Most High;\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Colossians\\3:2-2",id:"101",title:"Thoughts",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\3:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  Set your mind on the things that are above, not on the things that are on the earth.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Psalms\\19:14-14",id:"102",title:"Thoughts/Words",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\19:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Let the words of my mouth and the meditation of my heart be acceptable in your sight, Yahweh, my rock, and my redeemer.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"John\\14:1-1",id:"103",title:"Trust",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  {I}{B}Don't let your heart be troubled. Believe in God. Believe also in me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Proverbs\\3:5-6",id:"104",title:"Trust in God",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:5-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Trust in Yahweh with all your heart, and don't lean on your own understanding.\r {BR}6  In all your ways acknowledge him, and he will make your paths straight.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"Ephesians\\4:25-25",id:"105",title:"Truth",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  Therefore, putting away falsehood, speak truth each one with his neighbor. For we are members of one another.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"James\\1:5-8",id:"106",title:"Wisdom/Prayer",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\James\\1:5-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  But if any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all liberally and without reproach; and it will be given to him.\r {BR}6  But let him ask in faith, without any doubting, for he who doubts is like a wave of the sea, driven by the wind and tossed.\r {BR}7  For let that man not think that he will receive anything from the Lord.\r {BR}8  He is a double-minded man, unstable in all his ways.\r {BR}{BR}"},{scriptures:"1 Peter\\5:7-7",id:"107",title:"Worry",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\5:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  casting all your worries on him, because he cares for you.\r {BR}{BR}"}],tablename:"GreatVerses"};